Objectives:

Draw 2D walls in a 3D world.
Create and use an interactive viewing camera.
View the world from 1st or 3rd perspective.
Respond to keystrokes, and maintain a viewing state accordingly.
Assignment Specifications:

Make the maze 3D by extruding the lines into walls.
Draw each wall a different color.
When the user clicks ‘p’, see the world from a perspective viewpoint of your choosing.
When the user clicks ‘r’, see the world through the rat's eyes.
When the user clicks ‘t’, see the world from the top view (same as lines from last assignment).
See Going3D.cpp on the Notes page.
